    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "90ad27d950762a2a94d9520269ea99ceacf9d105b2cfd64f2974a15e4b9435a8",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "If $n$ and $k$ are fixed then can one say anything about the set of integers so represented?\n\nSee also [388] and [677]."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "bfca893b8714ed49bfd0499e3ce10c0f4abc1ea66c920f8e9ca9736d5279bf34",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Can every integer $N\\geq 2$ be written as\\[N=\\frac{\\prod_{1\\leq i\\leq k}(m+i)}{\\prod_{1\\leq i\\leq k}(n+i)}\\]for some $k\\geq 2$ and $m\\geq n+k$?"
    }
  },
